#. type=data_list
msgctxt "data_list"
msgid ""
"Close your eyes.\n"
"\n"
"Let's use the magic power of three to stay present and relax.\n"
"\n"
"Name three sounds you can hear right now.\n"
"Name three smells you can smell right now.\n"
"Name your three favourite foods.\n"
"\n"
"What are three things you can be grateful for right now? They do not have to be big.\n"
"\n"
"At the end of a tough day, thinking of three things to be grateful for can help us find the courage to try again tomorrow."
msgstr ""
"Fumba macho yako.\n"
"\n"
"Hebu tutumie maajabu ya namba tatu ili tuendelee kuwepo na kupumzika.\n"
"\n"
"Taja sauti tatu unazoweza kuzisikia sasa hivi.\n"
"Taja harufu tatu unazoweza kuzinusa sasa hivi.\n"
"Taja vyakula vitatu unavyovipenda.\n"
"\n"
"Je, ni mambo gani matatu unayoshukuru kuwa yapo sasa hivi? Si lazima yawe makubwa.\n"
"\n"
"Mwishoni mwa siku ngumu, kufikiria mambo matatu ya kushukuru kunaweza kutusaidia kupata ujasiri wa kujaribu tena kesho."

#. type=data_list
msgctxt "data_list"
msgid ""
"Children learn a lot from what we say, and how we say it. \n"
"\n"
"This week, we will look at the power of our words, and how we **TALK** to our children."
msgstr ""
"Watoto hujifunza mengi kutokana na yale tunayosema na jinsi tunavyoyasema.\n"
"\n"
"Wiki hii, tutaangalia kuhusu nguvu ya maneno na jinsi **TUNAVYOZUNGUMZA**  na watoto wetu.\n"
"\n"

#. type=data_list
msgctxt "data_list"
msgid ""
"Imagine someone tells you to go outside your house and walk to the end of your street. But they don’t tell you why, or what might happen when you get there.  \n"
"How does that make you feel? Confused? Scared? Hesitant?\n"
"Talking to your child about what is happening or why they should be doing something helps them to feel safe and to follow instructions."
msgstr ""
"Fikiria  mtu anakwambia uende nje ya nyumba yako utembee mpaka mwisho wa mtaa wako. Lakini hakwambii kwanini, au nini kinaweza kutokea ukifika  huko.\n"
"Hilo linakufanya ujiskieje? kuchanganyikiwa? kuogopa? Kusita?\n"
"Kuzungumza na mtoto wako kuhusu kile kinachotokea au kwanini  anapaswa kufanya jambo fulani humsaidia yeye kujiskia salama na kufuata maelekezo."

#. type=data_list
msgctxt "data_list"
msgid "Let’s see how **talking with your child** forms part of the garden image."
msgstr "Hebu tuone ambavyo **mazungumzo na mtoto wako** yanavyofanya sehemu ya taswira ya bustani."

#. type=data_list
msgctxt "data_list"
msgid ""
"The amount of water that plants receive determines how they grow. \n"
"In the same way - how much you talk to your child and what you say to them is important for their development."
msgstr ""
"Kiasi cha maji ambacho mmea hupokea kinapelekea namna mmea unavyokuwa.\n"
"\n"
"Vivyo hivyo - kwa kiasi gani unazungumza na mtoto wako na nini unawaambia ni muhimu kwa maendeleo yao.\n"
"\n"

#. type=data_list
msgctxt "data_list"
msgid ""
"Plants that don’t get enough water won’t grow. In the same way, children struggle when they don’t get enough information from their caregivers.\n"
"Just as harsh streams of water can damage small plants, a parent’s harsh words can interfere with a child’s growth. \n"
"That is why your words and how you use them play a powerful role in shaping your child."
msgstr ""
"Mimea ambayo haipati maji ya kutosha haitakuwa.Vivyo hivyo, watoto wanapata shida pale ambapo hawapati taarifa za kutosha  kutoka kwa walezi wao.\n"
"Kama vile vijito vya maji vikali vinavyoharibu mimea midogo. Maneno makali ya mzazi yanaweza kuharibu ukuaji wa mtoto.\n"
"Ndio maana maneno yako na jinsi unavyoyatumia yana jukumu kubwa la kumjenga mtoto.\n"
"\n"

#. type=data_list
msgctxt "data_list"
msgid "Here’s how to talk to your child:"
msgstr "Hapa ni jinsi unavyoweza kuzungumza na mtoto wako::"

#. type=data_list
msgctxt "data_list"
msgid ""
"**Name and describe things to your child**\n"
"\n"
"This helps your child understand what is happening."
msgstr ""
"**Taja na elezea vitu kwa mtoto wako**\n"
"\n"
"Hii humsaidia mtoto wako kuelewa nini kinachotokea."

#. type=data_list
msgctxt "data_list"
msgid ""
"Young children are still learning about the world and how it works. You can use every-day events and activities to talk to your child about different people, places, events and experiences. \n"
"Let’s use this picture as an example. You could point to the taxis and say: “Look, the taxis wait here to pick people up. They wait next to the marketplace because people might need a lift home after they have done their shopping.”\n"
"Or you could point to the market stands and say: “The market stands have umbrellas to keep the food out of the sun. This helps to keep the food cool and fresh.”\n"
"Or you could point to the woman and child and say: “They are looking out for cars before they cross the road.”"
msgstr ""
"Vijana wadogo bado wanaendelea kujifunza kuhusu ulimwengu na jinsi unavyofanya kazi. Unaweza kutumia matukio na shughuli za kila siku, kuzungumza na mtoto wako kuhusu watu tofauti, mahali, matukio na uzoefu.\n"
"Hembu tuitumie picha hii kama mfano. Unaweza kuelekeza kwenye taksi na kusema: “Tazama, taksi inasubiri hapa kuwachukua watu. Wanasubiri karibu na soko kwasababu watu wanaweza kuhitaji lifti ya kwenda nyumbani baada ya kumaliza kufanya manunuzi yao.”\n"
"Au unaweza kuwaonyesha kuelekea kwenye stendi ya soko na kusema:” Kituo cha soko kina miamvuli, kufanya chakula kisipigwe na jua. Hii inasaidia kukifanya chakula kipoe na kuwa vizuri.\n"
"Au unaweza kuonyesha kuelekea kwa mwanamke na mtoto na kusema: ”wanaangalia magari kabla hawajavuka barabara.”."

#. type=data_list
msgctxt "data_list"
msgid ""
"**Explain WHY** \n"
"\n"
"This helps your child understand cause and effect. It also helps them to follow instructions."
msgstr ""
"**Elezea KWANINI**\n"
"\n"
"Hii husaidia mtoto wako kuelewa sababisho na athari. Pia huwasaidia kufuata maelekezo."

#. type=data_list
msgctxt "data_list"
msgid ""
"Explaining “why” helps your child to see the bigger picture, and to understand the benefits of what they need to do.\n"
"Instead of saying: “Go brush your teeth now!”, you could say: “It’s time to brush your teeth. We brush our teeth because this keeps our teeth strong and healthy. We need strong and healthy teeth to eat and enjoy our food.”\n"
"By explaining to your child why they should brush their teeth, you help them to do what is expected of them."
msgstr ""
"Kuelezea “kwa nini” humsaidia mtoto wako kuona picha kubwa zaidi, na kuelewa manufaa ya kile anachohitaji kufanya.\n"
"Badala ya kusema: “Nenda kapige meno yako mswaki sasa!”, unaweza kusema: “Ni wakati wa kupiga mswaki. Tunapiga mswaki meno yetu kwa sababu hii hutunza uimara na afya ya meno yetu. Tunahitaji meno imara na yenye afya kula chakula chetu na kukifurahia\".\n"
"Kwa kumwelezea mtoto wako kwa nini wanapaswa kupiga mswaki, unawasaidia kufanya kile wanachotarajiwa."

#. type=data_list
msgctxt "data_list"
msgid ""
"**TALK with kindness** \n"
"\n"
"Use your words to build your child up, not to break them down."
msgstr ""
"**ZUNGUMZA kwa ukarimu**\n"
"\n"
"Tumia maneno yako kumjenga mtoto wako, sio kuwakatisha tamaa."

#. type=data_list
msgctxt "data_list"
msgid ""
"When something upsetting happens, use kind words to help your child learn.\n"
"If your child fell over, instead of saying “Look what happened! You hurt your knee because you were being careless and did not look where you were going!” \n"
"You could say in a kind voice: “Oh no – you fell down and hurt your knee – that must have given you a fright. It’s okay – we all fall down or get hurt sometimes. Next time, let’s try to be a bit more careful when we run outside.”"
msgstr ""
"Pale jambo fulani la kukasirisha linapotokea, tumia maneno ya ukarimu ili kumsaidia mtoto wako kujifunza. \n"
"Ikiwa mtoto wako ameanguka, badala ya kusema \"Angalia nini kimetokea! Umeumia goti kwa sababu ulikuwa mzembe na hukuangalia ulipokuwa unaenda!”\n"
"Unaweza kusema kwa sauti ya huruma: \"Loo hapana - ulianguka na kuumia goti lako - hiyo lazima iwe imekupa hofu. Ni sawa - sisi sote huwa tunaanguka chini au kuumia wakati mwingine. Wakati mwingine tujaribu kuwa waangalifu zaidi tunapokimbilia nje.”."

